Dr. Martel believes that 90% of patients who ask for death thank the medical staff for not doing their request after the palliative care team relieves their pain.
However, palliative care is not an absolute tool in the fight against pain.
According to Elsie Monroe, director of palliative care at the Greater Montreal Home Care Society, patients are not responsive to pain relief in 8% of cases.
At the end of life, doctors often resort to palliative sedation, where the patient sleeps until the moment of death, either occasionally or continuously.
