Germany abstained from voting on recognition of Palestine.
According to Stephen Sabo, an expert on U.S.-European relations, Berlin is balancing a narrow diplomatic path.
Deutsche Welle: Earlier this week, Germany first made it clear that it would vote against the Palestinians' request for observer status at the United Nations.
