I'm not retiring, I'm dying here because the volcano is my whole life.
Although the sulfur burns the throat and burns the eyes when the wind suddenly changes and catches the miners in the thick pillars of smoke coming out of the volcano, they are so resilient that no one complains about their severe illnesses... more serious, obviously, than their usual breathing problems, arthritis, knee pain and shoulder ulcers that have been deformed by the weight of the basket.
